{"tid":1301122,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"社會信用評級臨香港 必須加快BNO平權及歸英姿態！","createTime":"2019-07-09T14:24:02.000Z","updateTime":"2019-07-14T13:46:34.000Z","uid":268524,"like":49,"dislike":6,"uniUserReply":16,"replies":[{"pid":"1d3f7b9f29f7574bc4b071107269d1192abebaf8","tid":1301122,"uid":268524,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-09T14:24:02.000Z","msg":"小妹忍唔住要開第一個post喇， &quot;信用中國&quot;嗰度已經加咗香港做地方信用網站，即係已經預咗香港一份， 加快BNO平權有急切必要性。 <br />\n<br />\n小妹有一個idea， 各位巴絲睇下可唔可行: 嚟緊嘅遊行嗰度， 買100甚至1000支嘅龍獅旗，畀遊行嘅人一齊舉起， 做出更明顯嘅民意做歸英嘅姿態，要求BNO平權, 引外國關注上頭條，有冇得諗？ <br />\n<br />\n如果贊成， 有冇巴絲肯一齊舉旗， 做一個旗海去吸引傳媒注意？<br />\n<br />\n如果大家覺得有意思, 請幫忙推一推呢個idea, 感激不盡！ 如果唔可行都期望大家畀少少comment， 我接受任何批評, thanks!<br />\n<br />\n參考資料: <br />\n<br />\n信用中國<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.creditchina.gov.cn/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.creditchina.gov.cn%2F&d=aELkmJ%2FgRhSQUMA2B8lhBJ1DrXAeA17tgS6Eh9jzous%3D&h=8547f8bd\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.creditchina.gov.cn/</a><br />\n<br />\n香港已經在信用地方網站上<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/hJy9JfW.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FhJy9JfW.jpg&h=7e2e892e&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n【逆權運動】政府稱絕不在港實施社會信用評分 內地信用官網驚現預留港澳台連結<br />\n2019年7月9日<br />\n蘋果日報<br />\n<a href=\"https://hk.news.appledaily.com/local/realtime/article/20190709/59804740?utm_campaign=hkad_social_hk.nextmedia&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_source=facebook&amp;utm_content=link_post\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fhk.news.appledaily.com%2Flocal%2Frealtime%2Farticle%2F20190709%2F59804740%3Futm_campaign%3Dhkad_social_hk.nextmedia%26utm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_source%3Dfacebook%26utm_content%3Dlink_post&d=aELkmJ%2FgRhSQUMA2B8lhBJ1DrXAeA17tgS6Eh9jzous%3D&h=597439c7\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fhk.news.appledaily.com%2Flocal%2Frealtime%2Farticle%2F20190709%2F59804740%3Futm_campaign%3Dhkad_social_hk.nextmedia%26utm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_source%3Dfacebook%26utm_content%3Dlink_post&h=06313a2d\" target=\"_blank\">https://hk.news.appledaily.com/local/realtime/article/20190709/59804740?utm_campaign=hkad_social_hk.nextmedia&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_source=facebook&amp;utm_content=link_post</a><br />\n<br />\nThe Hong Kong protesters deserve Britain&rsquo;s full support <br />\n6 July 2019<br />\nThe Spectator<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.spectator.co.uk/2019/07/the-hong-kong-protesters-deserve-britains-full-support/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spectator.co.uk%2F2019%2F07%2Fthe-hong-kong-protesters-deserve-britains-full-support%2F&d=aELkmJ%2FgRhSQUMA2B8lhBJ1DrXAeA17tgS6Eh9jzous%3D&h=4de23e74\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.spectator.co.uk/2019/07/the-hong-kong-protesters-deserve-britains-full-support/</a><br />\n<br />\n//It was an error on the part of the John Major government not to grant Hong Kong&rsquo;s industrious people the right to settle in Britain before the handover. Most were condemned to be handed over to China along with their city &mdash; albeit with the promise that they would enjoy special privileges. In theory, Hong Kong citizens &mdash; unlike their counterparts on the mainland &mdash; have the right to protest against the Chinese Communist party. But some who exercised this supposed freedom have found themselves spirited away and sent to mainland China for detention. The trigger for the current protests, which this week included an invasion of the Hong Kong legislature, was an initiative brought in by Hong Kong Chief Executive Carrie Lam to create powers for felons to be extradited directly from Hong Kong to China.//<br />\n<br />\nBNO平權上不成障礙<br />\n黃世澤的筆記簿<br />\n2019年7月5日<br />\n<a href=\"https://martinoei.com/article/27688/bno-%e5%b9%b3%e6%ac%8a%e4%b8%8a%e4%b8%8d%e6%88%90%e9%9a%9c%e7%a4%99\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmartinoei.com%2Farticle%2F27688%2Fbno-%25e5%25b9%25b3%25e6%25ac%258a%25e4%25b8%258a%25e4%25b8%258d%25e6%2588%2590%25e9%259a%259